# get_irida_session
# perform form login to IRIDA and store session cookie for /ajax/ endpoint access
# reads credentials from Bitwarden via bw serve (must be running on 127.0.0.1:8087)
# exports IRIDA_SESSION_FILE pointing to the cookie jar
#
# NOTE: IRIDA's /login page is a React SPA - no HTML form, no CSRF token required.
#       Spring Security accepts a direct form POST to /login with no pre-flight.
#       302 to /irida-23.01.3/ = success; 302 to /login?error=true = bad credentials.
#
# example: get_irida_session && echo "session: ${IRIDA_SESSION_FILE}"
